Justification of Architecture Style
(Layered Architecture)
âœ… Definition of granularity:
->Granularity means how components are divided
->Each component handles one specific responsibility
->Components are logically separated, not mixed
->This improves clarity and modularity

âœ… How our project shows layered granularity:
->Email processing is split into independent modules
->Each module performs a single function
->Modules communicate through clear interfaces
->No module directly controls another moduleâ€™s internal logic

âœ… Component separation in the system:
->UI handles only user interaction
->Classification module handles only email categorization
->Response module handles only autoâ€‘reply generation
->Logger handles only data storage
->Admin module handles only system management
ðŸ‘‰ Each component is small, focused, and replaceable.

âœ… Independence of layers:
->Changing classification rules does not affect UI
->Changing UI does not affect logging
->Logging can be upgraded to a database without changing business logic
->Response templates can change without touching classifier
->This shows low coupling and high cohesion.

